glGtvy_uss5rGzTSma78gjW0es1-2hynu3AEjg55fsVmVtc01wIdhyf1ijr6G1r_nEfhfq1Qr2P47psossMSxztA_yrOO3H8lO1nOSvkDAmhT1hu5JIN4xS4SnyBFtLpr2Lm0fGALZNSPe3jsyjAvEBsJhPvOyedtb3Tfp9LtHjXJ-xQvb8rQthARKuSo8SN94UEEAH6-fdMEdyqAu7y9gWv5LWSv_59jcYkpjUSrAPdhziyLIcXGauNBEM3eu1wM3Bt2nDjJiqJ3tURp8UXWYzzJHGgACnspL0fkgdqbaeQfp_YQ8w88VazIUYvcYHWYha8a2XLFGoP897ym1eTWNz91lM4jqEif-0zRGBLHKg8Pjhr57-y3eqsAGUb7NO4_2_hQURQLuADNhkwUEl-O3ioErRa0N7hbJhIZm2zTqaNKEfy600QkNJ4fdUcJp756P9lvQ4Iepq_iUd4f0Gbv6jK7YSt1HcHeJpC4_11Cb0FPGWWomgpPmKzc3fImdqODa_NnB_tY1O8cx097fle4HRj0owUj89n66GDj923VoVc1NLWFueaxvbSZ7YQ8KnGmM6F5Z1SPw8v6Q75n8txcNV1Pwp15BEKFimASOY7YGWWVdOFbweKieOn59fnLVZCPX0ga3OtrwXF8Cliem3E3E3fFuMh85jVuoBCIS8kF3iiJbRDw4eoEIRFEntksk4IyENzA7IOwFFnRUln7iY2Lk_SNFpyEJne_FmSAHBh49iUBFBk1bDuO9ucDwla1ULN2Me--7xiLI1p2wq0ENkJxLEwCtAyUJKRW7E_OnOg8oZWiGcjpXDjhBgPYLQ6f3oFgiHudI_2Eob39pACYfm7OxyNA5TrqZMGvSLzs_XLI2PfUWmbCc2u_fx8RoYQS7hLNJz6qptu4TYbxKD4k-OWda-4x13FAY8-nH5qOoy3eVV4pE009wPtlBG9jNm7oVAnlSI15qdBnYL7ewGvzQZFztLKnC1DCthk9hPJF46u-KTH6OtCfTMoTKarbu10o-DFSsiZ_X10k-WWwBrA6-KW5GXttgCwEhdleJQGi3V_rmB6cs4mcoBX6sxyg8YgFh_7ldXwL9unkp9MNj6yZUXPMvydCjvGNqCrz4gcY-9S81Z_FoLE6aMRwOWqWA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating service locator issues**\\n\\nI’m wondering if the potential service locator is missing checksum algorithms, and whether MavenRepositorySystemUtils adds those. It looks like FileTransporterFactory needs a FileProcessor provided by resolver-impl. I think I need to import static assertj since it's top-level public and allows for no compile. However, I want to inspect the dynamic access report to confirm expectations. Also, looking at the DefaultArtifactDescriptorReader might help clarify parsing issues. I'm noticing possible version mismatches with resolver dependencies.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Testing artifact descriptor reader**\\n\\nI'm testing the artifactDescriptorReader with an ArtifactDescriptorRequest using a specific artifact. I’ll check if the result contains the correct artifact group, dependencies, and repositories. If the POM has repositories, I want to ensure those are recognized unless they're ignored in the session. I might need to include the repository in the POM and assert that it’s added correctly without requiring a network call. I’m also considering if I need to XML escape the repository URL.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Maven workspace processes**\\n\\nI'm focusing on using a temporary directory with subdirectories for testing. I need to check if the session defaults return the necessary configurations. Maybe I should inspect the repository listener, but I'm unsure if it's necessary. I want to test the `MavenWorkspaceReader` for dependency collection using a custom workspace reader without a file repository. I think implementing the workspace with the model for the artifact might complicate things, but it could be beneficial for testing.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating repository utilities**\\n\\nI’m considering if MavenRepositorySystemUtils might be deprecated, which is important because it involves using main public utilities. It's best to avoid deprecated APIs, but I’m not sure about newServiceLocator -- it might not be annotated. I didn't see anything when using javap. Perhaps I should look into using org.eclipse.aether.util.repository.SimpleArtifactDescriptorPolicy in case there’s a missing descriptor, but that doesn’t seem like the right route. I’ll keep researching this!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_3a26oIVHqV0rQRnQCg3YpcWN|fc_069332128ca7e23e016a4101d48c088195ba15b28a2a09399e", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.apache.maven/maven-resolver-provider/3.9.12/src/test/java/org_apache_maven/maven_resolver_provider/Maven_resolver_providerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_apache_maven.maven_resolver_provider;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport java.io.File;\nimport java.nio.charset.StandardCharsets;\nimport java.nio.file.Files;\nimport java.nio.file.Path;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport java.util.concurrent.atomic.AtomicInteger;\n\nimport org.apache.maven.model.Model;\nimport org.apache.maven.repository.internal.MavenRepositorySystemUtils;\nimport org.apache.maven.repository.internal.MavenWorkspaceReader;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.DefaultRepositorySystemSession;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.RepositorySystem;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.artifact.Artifact;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.artifact.DefaultArtifact;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.connector.basic.BasicRepositoryConnectorFactory;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.graph.Dependency;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.impl.DefaultServiceLocator;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.repository.LocalRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.repository.RemoteRepository;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.repository.RepositoryPolicy;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.ArtifactDescriptorRequest;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.ArtifactDescriptorResult;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.ArtifactRequest;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.ArtifactResult;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.VersionRangeRequest;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.resolution.VersionRangeResult;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.spi.connector.RepositoryConnectorFactory;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.spi.connector.transport.TransporterFactory;\nimport org.eclipse.aether.transport.file.FileTransporterFactory;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.io.TempDir;\n\npublic class Maven_resolver_providerTest {\n    @TempDir\n    Path tempDirectory;\n\n    @Test\n    void serviceLocatorResolvesMavenArtifactDescriptorFromHermeticFileRepository() throws Exception {\n        Path remoteRepositoryDirectory = tempDirectory.resolve(\"remote-descriptor-repository\");\n        Path localRepositoryDirectory = tempDirectory.resolve(\"local-descriptor-repository\");\n        String remoteRepositoryUrl = remoteRepositoryDirectory.toUri().toString();\n        writePom(remoteRepositoryDirectory, \"com.acme\", \"demo\", \"1.0.0\", \"\"\"\n                <project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\"\n                         xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n                         xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n                  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n                  <groupId>com.acme</groupId>\n                  <artifactId>demo</artifactId>\n                  <version>1.0.0</version>\n                  <name>Fixture descriptor</name>\n                  <properties>\n                    <runtime.version>1.1.0</runtime.version>\n                  </properties>\n                  <dependencyManagement>\n                    <dependencies>\n                      <dependency>\n                        <groupId>com.acme</groupId>\n                        <artifactId>managed-lib</artifactId>\n                        <version>2.0.0</version>\n                        <scope>compile</scope>\n                      </dependency>\n                    </dependencies>\n                  </dependencyManagement>\n                  <dependencies>\n                    <dependency>\n                      <groupId>com.acme</groupId>\n                      <artifactId>runtime-lib</artifactId>\n                      <version>${runtime.version}</version>\n                      <scope>runtime</scope>\n                      <optional>true</optional>\n                    </dependency>\n                  </dependencies>\n                  <repositories>\n                    <repository>\n                      <id>fixture-child</id>\n                      <url>%s</url>\n                    </repository>\n                  </repositories>\n                </project>\n                \"\"\".formatted(remoteRepositoryUrl));\n\n        RepositorySystem repositorySystem = newRepositorySystem();\n        DefaultRepositorySystemSession session = newSession(repositorySystem, localRepositoryDirectory);\n        RemoteRepository remoteRepository = repository(\"fixture\", remoteRepositoryUrl);\n        Artifact artifact = new DefaultArtifact(\"com.acme:demo:jar:1.0.0\");\n        ArtifactDescriptorRequest request = new ArtifactDescriptorRequest(artifact, List.of(remoteRepository), \"project\");\n\n        ArtifactDescriptorResult result = repositorySystem.readArtifactDescriptor(session, request);\n\n        assertThat(result.getArtifact().getGroupId()).isEqualTo(\"com.acme\");\n        assertThat(result.getArtifact().getArtifactId()).isEqualTo(\"demo\");\n        assertThat(result.getArtifact().getVersion()).isEqualTo(\"1.0.0\");\n        assertThat(result.getDependencies())\n                .extracting(Dependency::getArtifact)\n                .extracting(Artifact::toString)\n                .containsExactly(\"com.acme:runtime-lib:jar:1.1.0\");\n        assertThat(result.getDependencies())\n                .singleElement()\n                .satisfies(dependency -> {\n                    assertThat(dependency.getScope()).isEqualTo(\"runtime\");\n                    assertThat(dependency.isOptional()).isTrue();\n                });\n        assertThat(result.getManagedDependencies())\n                .extracting(Dependency::getArtifact)\n                .extracting(Artifact::toString)\n                .containsExactly(\"com.acme:managed-lib:jar:2.0.0\");\n        assertThat(result.getRepositories()).extracting(RemoteRepository::getId).contains(\"fixture-child\");\n        assertThat(localRepositoryDirectory.resolve(\"com/acme/demo/1.0.0/demo-1.0.0.pom\")).exists();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void versionRangeResolutionReadsMavenMetadataFromFileRepository() throws Exception {\n        Path remoteRepositoryDirectory = tempDirectory.resolve(\"remote-version-repository\");\n        Path localRepositoryDirectory = tempDirectory.resolve(\"local-version-repository\");\n        writeMetadata(remoteRepositoryDirectory, \"com.acme\", \"demo\", \"\"\"\n                <metadata>\n                  <groupId>com.acme</groupId>\n                  <artifactId>demo</artifactId>\n                  <versioning>\n                    <latest>2.1.0</latest>\n                    <release>2.1.0</release>\n                    <versions>\n                      <version>0.9.0</version>\n                      <version>1.0.0</version>\n                      <version>1.1.0</version>\n                      <version>2.1.0</version>\n                    </versions>\n                    <lastUpdated>20240628000000</lastUpdated>\n                  </versioning>\n                </metadata>\n                \"\"\");\n\n        RepositorySystem repositorySystem = newRepositorySystem();\n        DefaultRepositorySystemSession session = newSession(repositorySystem, localRepositoryDirectory);\n        RemoteRepository remoteRepository = repository(\"fixture\", remoteRepositoryDirectory.toUri().toString());\n        Artifact rangeArtifact = new DefaultArtifact(\"com.acme:demo:jar:[1.0.0,2.0.0)\");\n        VersionRangeRequest request = new VersionRangeRequest(rangeArtifact, List.of(remoteRepository), \"range-test\");\n\n        VersionRangeResult result = repositorySystem.resolveVersionRange(session, request);\n\n        assertThat(result.getVersions()).extracting(Object::toString).containsExactly(\"1.0.0\", \"1.1.0\");\n        assertThat(result.getRepository(result.getVersions().get(0))).isEqualTo(remoteRepository);\n        assertThat(localRepositoryDirectory.resolve(\"com/acme/demo/maven-metadata-fixture.xml\")).exists();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void artifactResolutionDownloadsUsingMavenLayoutAndCachesInLocalRepository() throws Exception {\n        Path remoteRepositoryDirectory = tempDirector